WEBVTT

04:01.080 --> 04:02.122
Tickets.

04:03.540 --> 04:05.334
Tickets.

04:06.335 --> 04:07.962
Tickets, please.

04:08.963 --> 04:11.173
Tickets. Tickets.

04:15.261 --> 04:17.596
Thank you. Tickets.

04:18.055 --> 04:20.099
Is it far to Tucumcari?

04:20.224 --> 04:22.268
We should pass there
in about three or four minutes.

04:22.393 --> 04:23.686
Thanks.

04:23.811 --> 04:27.147
Well, uh... excuse me,
but you've made a mistake, Reverend.

04:27.273 --> 04:29.358
I couldn't help hearing
you're going to Tucumcari.

04:29.483 --> 04:32.945
I peddle goods around here,
and I better tell you you're on the wrong train.

04:37.116 --> 04:39.910
I think the nearest stop
to Tucumcari is Amarillo.

04:40.035 --> 04:44.039
By getting off at Santa Fe
and returning by way of Amarillo,

04:44.164 --> 04:47.084
you should be able to get
right where you're... going.

04:49.503 --> 04:53.882
You see, the train doesn't stop
at Tucumcari.

05:03.976 --> 05:06.353
This train'll stop at Tucumcari.

05:32.087 --> 05:34.340
Take it easy, everybody!

05:35.049 --> 05:37.051
Why'd you stop?
Something's gone wrong?

05:37.176 --> 05:39.595
Somebody pulled the emergency cord.

05:49.938 --> 05:53.359
Hey, mister, you just can't pull
the emergency cord and jump off.

05:53.484 --> 05:56.653
Tell me, why'd you stop that train?
If you want to get off, you...

05:57.446 --> 05:59.865
Well, the railroad company
would be mighty pleased

05:59.990 --> 06:02.201
to make any arrangements
for any passenger

06:02.326 --> 06:04.370
if you want to get off here, sir.

06:04.495 --> 06:07.122
I did get off. Thanks.

06:09.792 --> 06:11.418
All right, let's go!

06:11.543 --> 06:13.629
Go ahead! Let's go!

06:46.620 --> 06:50.290
Guy passed by here in person
and added on those two zeros.

06:50.416 --> 06:52.709
He was spitting mad
when he saw what they was offering.

06:52.835 --> 06:54.128
He wasn't flattered.

06:54.253 --> 06:57.131
He said, "A measly thousand bucks
for me is much too little.

06:57.256 --> 07:00.134
"I'm worth a lot more than that."

07:00.259 --> 07:04.221
That's right. He said that,
and then he added the zeros on the thousand.

07:05.222 --> 07:08.767
There isn't anyone got the guts
to face that killer, eh?

07:17.484 --> 07:21.029
At least it's been that way till now.

08:02.237 --> 08:04.198
Where is he? Huh?

08:18.837 --> 08:20.631
Where is he?

08:28.347 --> 08:30.474
I've no idea where he'd be today.

08:52.955 --> 08:54.623
- Hold still.
- But, Guy...

08:54.748 --> 08:56.124
Hold still, I said.

08:56.250 --> 08:57.918
You hurt me
with those hands of yours.

08:58.043 --> 09:00.712
- Then do as I tell you.
- Stop it!

09:00.837 --> 09:02.589
Now see,
you've made me drop the soap.

09:04.925 --> 09:08.762
- Wait, I'll get it for you.
- You're killing me.

09:10.514 --> 09:12.558
Oh, look. What's that?

09:54.975 --> 09:56.768
Pardon me, ma'am.

11:28.944 --> 11:30.320
I'll kill you for this.

11:41.581 --> 11:44.167
There you are.
A thousand dollars.

11:54.720 --> 11:56.096
What do you know about Cavanagh?

11:57.097 --> 12:00.434
About a week ago,
he was seen at White Rocks.

12:00.559 --> 12:02.269
Thanks.

12:02.394 --> 12:04.980
If it's of any interest to you,

12:05.105 --> 12:07.649
somebody else dropped in
to see me about him.

12:09.192 --> 12:12.404
- Who?
- I'd never seen him before.

12:12.529 --> 12:15.449
His name is Manco.

13:46.081 --> 13:47.999
Light?

13:50.335 --> 13:52.712
You know Baby Cavanagh?

13:55.924 --> 13:58.760
Now tell me,
you know where I can find him?

14:05.517 --> 14:08.562
There, at that table.

14:08.687 --> 14:10.939
He's got his back to you.

14:14.442 --> 14:16.403
Thanks.

15:22.135 --> 15:24.054
Two cards.

16:03.385 --> 16:04.719
Didn't hear what the bet was.

16:09.599 --> 16:11.434
Your life.

16:39.504 --> 16:42.173
Alive or dead, it's your choice.

16:45.927 --> 16:47.804
Let Red go.

17:24.758 --> 17:27.677
Two thousand dollars.
It's a lot of money.

17:28.136 --> 17:30.055
Takes me three years to earn it.

17:30.180 --> 17:34.476
Tell me, isn't a sheriff
supposed to be courageous, loyal,

17:34.601 --> 17:36.352
and above all, honest?

17:37.103 --> 17:39.564
Yeah, that he is.

17:51.785 --> 17:54.454
I think you people need a new sheriff.

20:55.009 --> 20:56.511
Hughie!

21:13.987 --> 21:15.697
<i>Hasta luego.</i>

21:17.073 --> 21:18.449
<i>Amigo.</i>

21:33.256 --> 21:35.008
How are you, Niño?

21:35.133 --> 21:37.260
Better when I see you.

21:50.315 --> 21:52.233
Go on. Go ahead.

22:14.505 --> 22:16.049
Open it.

22:34.734 --> 22:37.945
- What's up? Who is it?
- Rodriguez, señor.

22:57.840 --> 22:59.675
Argh!

23:10.061 --> 23:12.730
You, come along.

23:27.912 --> 23:29.747
I'm letting you live, hero.

23:29.872 --> 23:32.792
That's so you can tell everybody
you've seen what takes place here.

24:31.684 --> 24:33.895
For the lousy money.

24:34.604 --> 24:37.064
No. No, no.

24:41.986 --> 24:44.530
You took money to put me behind bars.

24:47.783 --> 24:49.494
You should've killed me when you could.

24:50.495 --> 24:52.288
It would be better for you.

24:53.414 --> 24:55.625
And for them.

24:58.753 --> 25:01.047
How old is the boy?

25:05.051 --> 25:06.886
How old is the boy, I asked?

25:08.012 --> 25:09.514
He's 18 months now.

25:10.932 --> 25:13.226
Just the time that I was in jail.

25:16.437 --> 25:18.648
- You used the reward that you got...
- Oh, no! No, no.

25:18.773 --> 25:21.275
...to start raising a family.

25:22.944 --> 25:26.489
And that's why I feel
your family is partly mine.

25:27.782 --> 25:30.076
I'll take my part now.

25:30.201 --> 25:31.953
Outside.

25:35.831 --> 25:38.709
They're both innocent.
Please let them go.

25:38.834 --> 25:41.420
I was the one. You know that.

25:43.297 --> 25:45.091
Oh, no.

26:03.234 --> 26:04.569
No!

26:07.905 --> 26:09.907
I know.

26:10.032 --> 26:12.827
I'm sure you hate me just enough.

26:34.974 --> 26:37.560
This time you'll have a chance to shoot me,
but not in the back.

26:41.647 --> 26:43.441
Let go.

26:48.904 --> 26:51.532
When you hear the music finish, begin.

26:53.159 --> 26:54.702
Or do you think you can?

26:58.164 --> 27:00.333
Let's start.

28:56.365 --> 28:58.367
Now.

29:37.031 --> 29:39.742
- Check those figures again.
- Yes, sir.

29:42.787 --> 29:45.372
Good day, sir. Good afternoon.

29:45.498 --> 29:47.208
Mortimer.

29:47.958 --> 29:51.295
- Douglas Mortimer.
- Mortimer. Virginia, isn't it?

29:51.420 --> 29:53.839
- Carolina.
- That's right, Carolina.

29:53.964 --> 29:56.091
Can I help in some way?

29:56.217 --> 30:00.179
- I'm looking for a first-class bank.
- Oh, but exactly.

30:00.304 --> 30:01.680
Yeah.

30:01.806 --> 30:05.518
The largest and most secure bank
in the territory.

30:05.643 --> 30:08.979
Well, Mr Mortimer, I want to assure you
our bank here has everything,

30:09.104 --> 30:10.731
all the safeguards you're looking for.

30:10.856 --> 30:14.193
I don't doubt that,
but I have a large sum to deposit.

30:14.318 --> 30:16.445
Now, suppose I'm a bandit.

30:19.156 --> 30:21.033
A... bandit?

30:21.158 --> 30:24.286
A very dangerous bandit
with a gang of killers.

30:24.870 --> 30:28.916
Now, what would be
the most impossible bank for me to rob?

30:29.041 --> 30:32.628
In your case, the one bank
I would suggest is the Bank of El Paso.

30:32.753 --> 30:35.047
Not even Indio
would dare to attack that one.

30:35.172 --> 30:38.467
It's not a bank.
It's a fortress there.

30:42.638 --> 30:46.267
- What time's the next train for El Paso?
- 11:30.

30:46.392 --> 30:48.978
I'll telegraph to my colleague
in the Bank of El Paso

30:49.103 --> 30:50.813
that you're going to arrive.

30:50.938 --> 30:52.106
Thanks.

31:16.755 --> 31:19.633
Hey, mister.
Captain. General. Welcome.

31:19.758 --> 31:23.012
Do you need a stable or a room?
Do you want to take a bath?

31:23.137 --> 31:24.680
My name is Fernando.

31:24.805 --> 31:27.641
The stable is right here,
and that is your hotel.

31:29.143 --> 31:31.687
Why this hotel and not some other?

31:31.812 --> 31:34.440
You probably wouldn't like
that other place as much, señor.

31:34.565 --> 31:37.192
You'd have to spend half the night
shooting cockroaches.

31:37.318 --> 31:39.737
At this hotel,
the rooms will cost you so much less.

31:39.862 --> 31:42.239
And there's a landlady
at this one, señor.

31:43.532 --> 31:46.201
- Married?
- Yes, but she doesn't care.

32:04.970 --> 32:08.515
That's the bank.
As soon as I get some money, I'll put it in.

32:08.641 --> 32:11.185
Well, you're gonna have to earn it first.

32:12.561 --> 32:14.146
I have 50 cents here for you

32:14.271 --> 32:18.233
if you'll let me know when anybody
you've never seen before here in El Paso

32:18.359 --> 32:19.860
comes to town.

32:19.985 --> 32:23.238
At the hotel, señor.
A stranger just came out of there.

32:30.037 --> 32:33.916
Where's he staying?

32:41.006 --> 32:43.133
The hotel.

32:46.679 --> 32:49.306
Let me know if you see
any more strangers, hmm?

32:49.431 --> 32:51.767
Sure, señor.

33:06.740 --> 33:08.242
Help you, sir?

33:08.367 --> 33:10.369
I want the room right above.

33:10.494 --> 33:13.497
I'm sorry, it's occupied. It's too bad.

33:13.622 --> 33:15.916
The hotel's filled to capacity.

33:16.041 --> 33:18.377
I'm sorry.
The room you want is our best.

33:18.502 --> 33:21.088
- It's always occupied.
- By who?

33:21.880 --> 33:24.633
Check the register.
Mary!

33:27.052 --> 33:29.430
It's Señor Martinez.

33:37.813 --> 33:39.440
It's free now.

33:40.024 --> 33:41.275
That room is taken!

33:42.943 --> 33:44.903
I'll see to it.

33:49.616 --> 33:51.744
He's nothing but a wild, vicious animal.

33:52.870 --> 33:55.039
He's tall, isn't he?

33:58.959 --> 34:01.086
You're just dirty!

34:12.973 --> 34:15.392
Proprietor, quick! My bill!

34:16.477 --> 34:18.729
I want my bill!

34:19.897 --> 34:22.775
- Before he comes down here, give me my bill.
- Oh, no. There's no need to check out.

34:22.900 --> 34:24.985
I assure you, everything's
gonna be all right, Mr Martinez.

34:25.110 --> 34:27.780
I'll give you another room immediately.
It's the best in the whole hotel, the best.

34:27.905 --> 34:30.199
- No, you don't understand.
- We'll let him have the bridal suite.

34:30.324 --> 34:32.034
No, no, Mary, the bill.
I'd like to stay, only I can't.

34:32.159 --> 34:33.869
Don't go, Mr Martinez.

34:33.994 --> 34:36.663
- I have an appointment elsewhere.
- Señor Martinez.

34:39.374 --> 34:41.794
Yes, señor.
What do you want?

34:47.341 --> 34:49.259
I don't wear 'em.

34:49.384 --> 34:51.845
I'm honored that you thought of me.
Thank you.

35:31.552 --> 35:32.553
Watch this.

35:57.828 --> 35:59.621
Hello, my friends.

36:00.998 --> 36:02.791
Hello, Indio.

36:02.916 --> 36:05.919
You see, I didn't waste a minute
coming here.

36:06.044 --> 36:08.922
Indio calls,
and Groggy comes running right away.

36:09.047 --> 36:10.340
And Sancho?

36:10.465 --> 36:14.303
If you're waiting for Sancho,
I'll go and come back in about four years.

36:14.428 --> 36:17.639
He's in prison for four years.

36:17.764 --> 36:21.560
No <i>amor.</i> No <i>dinero.</i> No sun.

36:24.438 --> 36:28.066
Bad for him.
Not so bad for the rest of us.

36:28.192 --> 36:31.278
A man who gets caught
doesn't deserve respect, huh?

36:33.405 --> 36:34.656
What's it all about, huh?

36:36.033 --> 36:37.451
Now, just listen.

36:41.663 --> 36:43.415
A bank at El Paso.

36:45.417 --> 36:46.668
Let's see.

36:46.793 --> 36:49.463
We'll say this is the inside of the bank.

36:50.589 --> 36:52.049
Niño is the safe.

36:52.174 --> 36:55.260
Which weighs three tons
and can't be opened with dynamite.

36:56.303 --> 36:58.639
There's the part with two cashiers.

36:59.598 --> 37:02.142
This is the manager's desk.

37:02.267 --> 37:05.020
Right in back
is a fancy cabinet containing bottles

37:05.145 --> 37:08.065
for offering drinks to the rich depositors.

37:09.691 --> 37:13.695
There's the main door,
and opposite they built a double wall.

37:13.820 --> 37:15.697
What happens, Groggy?

37:15.822 --> 37:19.910
Let's say you've already killed
the two cashiers and the manager.

37:20.035 --> 37:23.372
And for the next few minutes,
you're the boss of the bank.

37:24.289 --> 37:25.999
Now what?

37:26.124 --> 37:28.460
The time's been wasted, Indio.

37:30.712 --> 37:32.714
Right, a waste of time.

37:32.839 --> 37:35.884
Especially, Groggy,
to blast open that damn iron safe,

37:36.009 --> 37:38.387
we'd have to be using
so much dynamite

37:38.512 --> 37:41.306
that the whole bank
would just disappear.

37:41.431 --> 37:43.684
And you'd all go up with it.

37:44.434 --> 37:48.105
And besides,
the presence of a safe alone

37:48.230 --> 37:51.233
doesn't always signify
that there is money inside.

37:52.693 --> 37:55.487
To help you understand what I mean...

37:57.072 --> 38:01.618
...I would like to relate a nice little parable.

38:04.079 --> 38:07.332
Once upon a time there was a carpenter.

38:09.167 --> 38:11.503
You don't think a carpenter
can make money, eh?

38:12.296 --> 38:14.631
No? You're wrong.

38:15.924 --> 38:20.846
This one did well
because he was a builder of safes.

38:21.888 --> 38:24.224
There was a banker once

38:24.349 --> 38:26.977
who decided
he must have his iron safe disguised

38:27.102 --> 38:30.355
to look like a wood cabinet.

38:33.608 --> 38:35.694
To get it made,

38:35.819 --> 38:39.281
the banker goes to our carpenter
for the job,

38:39.406 --> 38:43.327
and one day, as destiny has it,

38:43.452 --> 38:46.038
the carpenter's in El Paso.

38:46.163 --> 38:49.499
He happens to walk into the bank there,
and what does he find?

38:50.500 --> 38:52.377
The cabinet.

38:52.502 --> 38:55.839
Since he'd worked on the cabinet,
he spotted it right away.

38:56.506 --> 38:58.425
From that day on,
he couldn't work anymore.

38:59.634 --> 39:01.636
Pity, because...

39:02.596 --> 39:05.307
...there was something he had to do.

39:05.432 --> 39:07.434
There was this crazy idea.

39:08.310 --> 39:10.145
And it stayed.

39:10.937 --> 39:12.773
And it stayed.

39:14.358 --> 39:16.693
To put his hands on the money inside.

39:17.486 --> 39:19.279
Get in there and grab all the money.

39:20.405 --> 39:24.785
Sure, you think that carpenter
was lucky the way things work out.

39:24.910 --> 39:27.371
That he was lucky to go in just that bank.

39:28.080 --> 39:29.956
It wasn't true.

39:31.333 --> 39:33.585
His good fortune stopped that day.

39:34.294 --> 39:37.923
Because later, as a prisoner...

39:40.675 --> 39:42.552
...he ran into me.

39:47.766 --> 39:51.478
The carpenter told me the story,
and I tell you.

39:57.567 --> 39:59.861
The money isn't in the safe.
It's right in this.

40:03.365 --> 40:05.033
Almost a million dollars in it.

40:08.662 --> 40:10.705
Your colleague
in Tucumcari told me

40:10.831 --> 40:14.459
that this bank has the largest deposits
in the whole state.

40:14.584 --> 40:16.545
Yes, that's correct, Mr Mortimer.

40:16.670 --> 40:21.508
Here at the bank at El Paso we have
half a million dollars reserve on hand.

40:23.969 --> 40:25.220
I see.

40:25.345 --> 40:28.181
You sure this bank is secure enough
to hold that much?

40:28.306 --> 40:31.184
From the moment your money's
on deposit here, Mr Mortimer,

40:31.309 --> 40:32.936
you can sleep without any worries.

40:35.814 --> 40:37.524
Besides...

40:38.358 --> 40:41.153
...when the bank is closed,
an armed guard always remains here,

40:41.278 --> 40:43.947
and a patrol is on guard outside.

40:44.072 --> 40:47.701
Even the Bank of San Francisco
isn't that well protected.

40:47.826 --> 40:51.037
Exactly. Now, the truth is,
Mr Mortimer...

40:52.747 --> 40:55.083
...to try robbing us would be so futile

40:55.208 --> 40:58.253
that only a complete fool
would attempt it.

40:58.378 --> 41:00.422
Yeah.

41:00.547 --> 41:02.883
Or a complete madman.

41:13.768 --> 41:15.854
Get out of the way! Get out of here!

42:01.399 --> 42:03.568
More news, <i>amigo.</i>

42:05.612 --> 42:08.198
Another stranger in town?

42:08.323 --> 42:11.159
Yes.
And I know something else.

42:16.706 --> 42:19.626
There was another stranger
I didn't tell you about.

42:20.627 --> 42:23.380
Listen to me, you sawed-off little runt!

42:23.505 --> 42:26.091
I want to know
how many men there are all together.

42:26.216 --> 42:28.260
Well, there were two.
Now there's two more.

42:28.385 --> 42:30.220
Where?

42:31.054 --> 42:32.722
In the saloon.

44:43.061 --> 44:44.270
Whiskey.

44:44.396 --> 44:47.732
Listen, mister, why do you choose
my place to commit suicide?

44:47.857 --> 44:50.735
I know that man.
It's a miracle you're alive.

44:51.486 --> 44:55.240
Why should a man walk around with a pistol
and then let himself be insulted?

44:55.365 --> 44:59.285
- It's mighty strange.
- Well, sir, if the hunchback didn't shoot you,

44:59.411 --> 45:03.206
he had a very, very
important reason, that's all.

45:04.290 --> 45:06.501
I was thinking that myself.

46:06.311 --> 46:09.147
One, two,

46:09.272 --> 46:13.443
three, and four, and five.

46:13.568 --> 46:17.655
<i>Seis, siete, ocho,</i>

46:17.781 --> 46:19.908
<i>nueve, diez.</i>

46:21.034 --> 46:24.370
Eleven, twelve, thirteen,

46:24.496 --> 46:27.999
fourteen, fifteen, sixteen,

46:28.124 --> 46:32.545
seventeen, eighteen, nineteen,

46:32.670 --> 46:36.841
twenty, twenty-one, twenty-two,

46:36.966 --> 46:43.306
twenty-three, twenty-four, twenty-five,
twenty-six.

46:43.431 --> 46:47.936
Twenty-seven, twenty-eight,
twenty-nine,

46:48.061 --> 46:51.022
thirty, thirty-one,

46:51.147 --> 46:54.734
thirty-two, and thirty-three.

48:35.084 --> 48:37.086
No. No, no.

48:39.380 --> 48:41.591
- All right, now.
- Argh!

48:42.800 --> 48:45.511
I don't know him! I don't know him!
I don't know him!

48:45.637 --> 48:47.555
Come on, now, you know everybody.

48:47.680 --> 48:51.351
I don't know anybody anymore!
I'm dead! Understand?

48:51.476 --> 48:53.937
Well, there was a time
when I knew everybody.

48:54.062 --> 48:56.773
That was a long time ago
when all this was prairie.

48:56.898 --> 48:58.691
But in these days,
everybody's in a hurry.

48:58.816 --> 49:00.985
That's right, with your damned
good-for-nothing trains!

49:01.110 --> 49:04.572
Your damn trains!
Toot-toot-toot-twee!

49:05.365 --> 49:06.991
Disgusting!

49:07.116 --> 49:09.661
One day, someone from the railroad
comes here to see me,

49:09.786 --> 49:13.122
and he says, "Prophet, the railway's
gonna go right past your house."

49:13.247 --> 49:15.667
"Ah, is that so?" I said.

49:15.792 --> 49:18.503
"Mm-hmm!
Yep, that right," he says.

49:18.628 --> 49:20.838
"All those trains
gonna go right past here.

49:20.964 --> 49:23.591
"And the best thing for you, Prophet,
is to sell your land to the company

49:23.716 --> 49:24.926
"or else we'll buy Baker's.

49:25.051 --> 49:26.719
"He lives next to your place,

49:26.844 --> 49:29.347
"and I'll put the tracks there
and that'll make you go crazy.

49:29.472 --> 49:32.183
"What do you say? Will you sell out
to our company, Prophet?"

49:32.308 --> 49:34.769
"Oh, is that so?" says I.

49:36.771 --> 49:39.065
He was very anxious for me to sell out.

49:39.190 --> 49:41.776
Oh! You know what I told him
about the railroad?

49:41.901 --> 49:44.696
You know what I told him
he could do with his railroad?

50:03.506 --> 50:06.592
You know what my decision
about selling was?

50:06.718 --> 50:09.512
- Well, you said no.
- You're right about that.

50:09.637 --> 50:11.472
No to him and his damn trains.

50:11.597 --> 50:13.641
I wouldn't! No!

50:13.766 --> 50:16.602
Look, listen to me, old man.

50:16.728 --> 50:18.354
You're supposed to be a prophet.

50:18.479 --> 50:21.566
I didn't come here
to listen to you rattle on about trains.

50:21.691 --> 50:24.986
I wanted to find out about this man.
It's obvious you don't know anything.

50:25.111 --> 50:26.612
No need to be insulting.

50:26.738 --> 50:29.323
If that's all you came here to do,
you can clear out of my house fast

50:29.449 --> 50:32.285
before I lose my temper.
Understand?

50:36.497 --> 50:39.125
Hey! Where you going, hmm?

50:41.919 --> 50:44.922
I guess I better leave
before you go and lose your temper.

50:45.673 --> 50:48.217
What's the matter with you?
Why are you so dang stupid?

50:48.342 --> 50:50.386
Hurry up.
Give me that pistol there.

50:50.970 --> 50:52.764
Yeah, right there behind you.

50:52.889 --> 50:54.557
Hurry!

50:54.682 --> 50:57.685
Yes, yes, that's the one.
Now, hand it over.

50:58.811 --> 51:01.856
That's it. Give me that gun.
The man you asked about.

51:01.981 --> 51:04.776
There's only one question,
how does he carry his gun, huh?

51:04.901 --> 51:07.695
- He wears it here, across his belly?
- Yeah.

51:07.820 --> 51:10.615
Well, why didn't you tell me that
in the first place, my boy.

51:10.740 --> 51:13.076
Of course I know the man
you're trying to find out about.

51:13.201 --> 51:14.911
Of course I know him.

51:15.036 --> 51:18.122
He's Colonel Douglas Mortimer.

51:18.247 --> 51:21.334
Mortimer, a brave man, a soldier.

51:22.001 --> 51:24.629
He was known
as the best shot in the Carolinas.

51:24.754 --> 51:26.380
A great soldier.

51:27.131 --> 51:30.051
Now he's reduced to being a bounty killer,
same as you.

51:30.176 --> 51:31.886
Because of trains.

51:32.011 --> 51:35.640
Because of the damn trains!
Damn them! Phooey!

53:01.767 --> 53:03.561
Take it to the station.

53:03.686 --> 53:05.938
The gentleman's leaving.

53:10.151 --> 53:11.485
Hold it.

53:14.572 --> 53:15.781
Take it back.

53:18.868 --> 53:21.204
Take it to the station.

53:23.706 --> 53:26.083
- Go inside.
- The station.

53:26.709 --> 53:28.920
Oh!

54:34.944 --> 54:37.280
Just like the games we know.

55:32.752 --> 55:35.212
- He's picking it up.
- A trick, maybe.

57:21.110 --> 57:26.407
How can somebody in my business
go around with a contraption like this?

57:26.532 --> 57:28.451
That contraption...

57:29.785 --> 57:32.246
...almost sent you to your grave.

57:33.956 --> 57:37.376
You're forgetting one thing, Colonel,
I was shooting at your hat.

57:37.501 --> 57:40.546
Well, I was only shooting at yours.

57:40.671 --> 57:43.299
But I recall firing first.

57:44.842 --> 57:46.719
Boy...

57:46.844 --> 57:49.889
I've reached almost fifty years of age
with my system.

57:50.014 --> 57:52.308
Not many men last long in these parts.

57:52.433 --> 57:55.478
How long do you expect to last?

57:55.603 --> 57:57.938
Mm! Much longer than that.

57:59.023 --> 58:02.693
When I get my hands on Indio
and that ten thousand dollars,

58:02.818 --> 58:06.405
I'm gonna buy myself a little place,
possibly retire.

58:06.530 --> 58:07.907
Yeah.

58:08.032 --> 58:10.951
Well, I don't believe
we ought to start another fight.

58:11.076 --> 58:14.538
- But you forget one small detail.
- What's that?

58:14.663 --> 58:16.957
I wanna get my hands on Indio, too.

58:17.082 --> 58:20.085
Sure, after me.

58:21.086 --> 58:23.339
Or before you.

58:23.464 --> 58:25.633
Or at the same time.

58:28.469 --> 58:30.888
Is that a proposition?

58:31.722 --> 58:34.099
An equal partnership.

58:34.225 --> 58:35.976
Why? Why should I?

58:36.101 --> 58:38.103
Well, I can think of three reasons.

58:38.229 --> 58:40.439
First is, there's fourteen of them.

58:40.564 --> 58:42.441
Yeah, that's a lot.

58:42.566 --> 58:44.443
- A lot for me.
- Yeah.

58:44.568 --> 58:46.529
No small number even for two of us.

58:46.654 --> 58:48.405
Second reason?

58:49.406 --> 58:51.575
Second reason?

58:54.078 --> 58:56.622
The second reason is,
you could make it fifteen to one.

58:56.747 --> 58:59.291
Don't forget
I wanna play in this game, too.

58:59.416 --> 59:03.587
As you're aware,
when two hunters go after the same prey,

59:03.712 --> 59:05.548
they usually end up
shooting each other in the back,

59:05.673 --> 59:08.259
and we don't want
to shoot each other in the back.

59:11.470 --> 59:13.806
Then the colonel dies, hmm?

59:16.058 --> 59:18.811
All right, I'll be generous.

59:19.812 --> 59:22.398
You can have the reward for Indio,

59:22.523 --> 59:24.608
and I'll take the reward
for the rest of the band.

59:26.485 --> 59:29.488
No. All wrong.

59:29.613 --> 59:31.490
No, Indio's worth ten thousand dollars,

59:31.615 --> 59:34.618
but the rest of the band
adds up to much more than that.

59:34.743 --> 59:38.205
Blackie's worth four,
Wild's worth three, Niño two.

59:38.330 --> 59:40.583
Niño's one.

59:42.543 --> 59:45.004
Well, Frisco's worth two.

59:45.129 --> 59:47.923
Well, that's ten thousand.

59:48.048 --> 59:52.761
Yeah, but... there's a few more
that'll add up to more than that, I'm sure.

59:52.886 --> 59:56.223
- How do you know that?
- I have my information, Colonel.

59:56.348 --> 59:58.517
You know,
when all's said and done,

59:58.642 --> 01:00:02.187
I think I might just take you up
on your proposition.

01:00:04.565 --> 01:00:06.775
Let's drink to this partnership.

01:00:10.446 --> 01:00:13.866
To the partnership,
with no tricks, of course.

01:00:14.950 --> 01:00:17.077
No tricks.

01:00:20.914 --> 01:00:23.626
Now, then, you realise, of course,

01:00:23.751 --> 01:00:26.587
we're gonna have to figure out
some way to get them in the middle.

01:00:27.338 --> 01:00:29.340
Yep.

01:00:29.465 --> 01:00:33.677
One from the outside, one from the inside.
There's no other way.

01:00:33.802 --> 01:00:36.972
One of us will have to join Indio's band.

01:00:38.057 --> 01:00:41.310
Why are you looking at me
when you say "one of us"?

01:00:41.435 --> 01:00:42.645
Because they don't know you.

01:00:43.354 --> 01:00:46.315
Wild sees me,
and his hump will catch on fire.

01:00:48.901 --> 01:00:53.697
Tell me, Colonel, how do you propose
that I join up with Indio?

01:00:53.822 --> 01:00:56.825
Maybe bring him a bunch of roses?

01:00:56.950 --> 01:01:01.705
Well, you could do that,
but I'd suggest you take him Sancho Perez.

01:01:01.830 --> 01:01:04.875
- Who's Sancho Perez?
- A friend of Indio's.

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:09.380
Right now he's cooling off.
He's cooling off in Alamogordo jail.

01:01:09.505 --> 01:01:11.674
How do you know all this?

01:01:13.133 --> 01:01:15.844
I've got my information, too.

01:01:17.596 --> 01:01:22.059
Naturally, you'll have to arrange
for his, uh... release.

01:01:24.561 --> 01:01:26.480
Naturally.

01:01:27.648 --> 01:01:31.276
Tell me, Colonel,
were you ever young?

01:01:33.821 --> 01:01:35.531
Yup.

01:01:35.656 --> 01:01:37.658
And just as reckless as you.

01:01:41.328 --> 01:01:44.289
Then one day something happened.

01:01:44.415 --> 01:01:46.333
Made life very precious to me.

01:01:47.292 --> 01:01:49.294
What's that?

01:01:53.674 --> 01:01:56.135
Or is the question indiscreet?

01:01:57.052 --> 01:01:59.096
No.

01:01:59.221 --> 01:02:01.390
Your question isn't indiscreet.

01:02:02.641 --> 01:02:04.810
But the answer could be.

01:05:18.754 --> 01:05:20.297
They told me you were put away.

01:05:20.422 --> 01:05:23.133
You'd be resting
for four long years in prison.

01:05:25.677 --> 01:05:29.765
No, Indio, for four weeks.
No more than four weeks.

01:05:31.516 --> 01:05:33.352
Sancho.

01:05:41.401 --> 01:05:44.738
- Who is that with you?
- He got me out.

01:05:44.863 --> 01:05:47.574
The man's a friend of mine.

01:05:53.956 --> 01:05:56.833
Why did he help you?
Did you ask him that?

01:05:57.834 --> 01:06:01.964
Huh! Yeah<i>. Amigo,</i>
why did you help me out?

01:06:03.757 --> 01:06:08.887
Well, there's such a big reward
being offered on all you gentlemen

01:06:09.012 --> 01:06:13.225
that I thought I might just tag along
on your next robbery.

01:06:13.350 --> 01:06:15.560
Might just turn you in to the law.

01:06:58.228 --> 01:07:00.147
<i>Amigo.</i>

01:07:01.481 --> 01:07:04.484
That's the one answer
that would prove you're all right.

01:07:07.029 --> 01:07:11.283
And you arrived just in time, too.
The job is already set.

01:07:11.408 --> 01:07:13.201
It's tomorrow.

01:07:13.952 --> 01:07:15.662
The place is...

01:07:16.538 --> 01:07:19.166
...the bank in El Paso.

01:07:21.001 --> 01:07:24.046
Not far from El Paso
there's a little town, Santa Cruz.

01:07:24.171 --> 01:07:31.011
Tomorrow, Blackie, Chico, Paco,
and... you, <i>amigo,</i>

01:07:31.136 --> 01:07:33.680
will rob the bank in Santa Cruz.

01:07:33.805 --> 01:07:36.975
Shoot, kill,
get every gun in the area after you

01:07:37.100 --> 01:07:39.061
especially those from El Paso.

01:07:39.728 --> 01:07:42.439
Any others around,
we'll take care of them.

01:07:44.191 --> 01:07:47.319
And then after the job,
we'll all meet again at Las Palmeras.

01:07:52.324 --> 01:07:53.909
Where are you going?

01:08:00.165 --> 01:08:03.460
Well, if there's gonna be
any shooting,

01:08:03.585 --> 01:08:05.712
I gotta get my rest.

01:08:22.562 --> 01:08:23.939
Hey, <i>amigo,</i>

01:08:24.064 --> 01:08:27.651
you know when you told that story
yesterday, I fell for it.

01:08:28.276 --> 01:08:30.070
Big joke, wasn't it, <i>amigo</i>?

01:08:39.246 --> 01:08:41.206
Who said I was joking?

01:08:43.083 --> 01:08:44.960
I don't get that. If it's true...

01:08:45.085 --> 01:08:47.045
Too bad you have to die.

01:08:52.175 --> 01:08:53.635
What is it?

01:09:49.941 --> 01:09:52.235
By now they should be at Santa Cruz.

01:10:34.361 --> 01:10:35.987
Listen, shorty...

01:10:39.741 --> 01:10:43.286
...Indio and his band
have just robbed the bank here in town.

01:10:43.411 --> 01:10:44.871
Now, why don't you just sit down

01:10:44.996 --> 01:10:47.832
and send out the alarm to El Paso
and the rest of the towns around here

01:10:47.958 --> 01:10:49.584
and warn them, right?

01:10:49.709 --> 01:10:52.420
But, mister,
I didn't hear any shots at the bank,

01:10:52.545 --> 01:10:55.799
- and I sure would have.
- You might hear one.

01:10:56.258 --> 01:10:57.634
The alarm.

01:11:40.593 --> 01:11:42.137
Easy now.

01:11:43.638 --> 01:11:46.016
They've robbed the bank at Santa Cruz!

01:11:47.100 --> 01:11:48.810
Follow me!

01:13:27.158 --> 01:13:29.327
Groggy, the telegraph wires.

01:13:37.961 --> 01:13:40.213
Giddy-up! Hiya!

01:15:23.691 --> 01:15:25.443
- Good day, gentlemen.
- Good day, sir.

01:15:25.568 --> 01:15:27.278
Good day.

01:15:29.489 --> 01:15:31.491
- Sir.
- Afternoon.

01:17:21.434 --> 01:17:23.269
The other side.

01:18:07.605 --> 01:18:09.482
Eleven,

01:18:09.607 --> 01:18:10.858
twelve...

01:18:13.945 --> 01:18:15.446
Fourteen.

01:20:57.108 --> 01:20:58.693
Let's go!

01:22:22.443 --> 01:22:24.820
What are you doing here?
You're not running away, are you?

01:22:24.946 --> 01:22:28.491
No, I'm not running away.
I'm going after them, and I'm going alone.

01:22:28.616 --> 01:22:30.242
Our partnership is dissolved.

01:22:30.368 --> 01:22:32.078
Now, boy,
let's wait and talk it over.

01:22:32.203 --> 01:22:34.080
Yeah?
Well, all we've done is talk.

01:22:34.205 --> 01:22:37.792
- I've been reasonable with no results.
- Now take it easy.

01:22:37.917 --> 01:22:39.961
We only knew the Santa Cruz part
of this plan.

01:22:40.086 --> 01:22:43.089
Well, you were the one
who had their strategy all worked out.

01:22:43.214 --> 01:22:46.175
- Now I'm gonna meet Indio.
- I see. I'd better go along.

01:22:46.926 --> 01:22:48.803
I'm going alone. Me.

01:22:48.928 --> 01:22:52.264
I have an appointment with Indio,
and I'm not gonna let anyone else interfere.

01:22:52.390 --> 01:22:55.267
- You certain about that?
- That's right, Colonel.

01:22:55.393 --> 01:22:58.270
All right, in that case, I'm sorry.

01:23:02.191 --> 01:23:03.609
That's not bad.

01:23:04.068 --> 01:23:06.654
Indio sent four men to Santa Cruz.

01:23:06.779 --> 01:23:09.657
One man returns,
a new man without a scratch.

01:23:09.782 --> 01:23:12.076
Mm-mm. Indio's no idiot.

01:23:12.201 --> 01:23:15.871
When you ride up to him again and show him
that little nick you got, he might believe you.

01:23:16.664 --> 01:23:18.708
And don't forget that as of today,

01:23:18.833 --> 01:23:21.419
the whole gang is worth
forty thousand dollars more.

01:23:21.544 --> 01:23:24.005
That's the reward offered by the bank
to get the money back.

01:23:24.839 --> 01:23:28.718
- Is the partnership operating again?
- Just how do you figure?

01:23:28.843 --> 01:23:33.556
Try to convince Indio to go north,
and then go along the Rio Bravo.

01:23:33.681 --> 01:23:36.434
It's a good spot for an ambush,
and we can get him between two fires.

01:23:36.559 --> 01:23:40.855
Yeah. You on the outside,
me on the inside, right?

01:23:41.397 --> 01:23:43.566
Mm-hmm. North?

01:23:47.862 --> 01:23:49.238
North.

01:24:08.215 --> 01:24:09.925
Hughie.

01:24:18.559 --> 01:24:22.480
Wait a minute. We need time to open it,
and this isn't the right place.

01:24:52.176 --> 01:24:53.636
And the others?

01:24:53.761 --> 01:24:55.930
- Dead?
- Yeah.

01:24:56.055 --> 01:25:00.893
After Santa Cruz, we headed for El Paso,
and they hit us from all sides.

01:25:02.144 --> 01:25:04.980
And you just saved your own skin,
isn't that right? You yellow...

01:25:25.000 --> 01:25:28.129
You did your part of it. Let's go.

01:25:28.254 --> 01:25:30.297
Which way are we headed?

01:25:31.173 --> 01:25:33.634
- North.
- North?

01:25:33.759 --> 01:25:35.928
Along Rio Bravo canyon?

01:25:36.053 --> 01:25:37.721
Why not?

01:25:38.764 --> 01:25:41.517
Seems like a good place
for an ambush to me.

01:25:43.310 --> 01:25:45.354
You know a better way to go?

01:25:45.479 --> 01:25:47.523
Yeah, south.

01:25:48.274 --> 01:25:50.734
Ride to the border?

01:25:50.860 --> 01:25:55.322
Yeah, they'll never expect you to cross
the border now that the alarm's been sent.

01:26:00.327 --> 01:26:01.495
No.

01:26:01.620 --> 01:26:03.289
Think we'll head east.

01:26:04.081 --> 01:26:07.418
There's a place I know about,
Agua Caliente.

01:26:07.918 --> 01:26:11.463
Here we are.
That's Agua Caliente.

01:26:11.964 --> 01:26:14.842
Yes, I have many friends here.

01:26:14.967 --> 01:26:17.845
It looks just like a morgue.

01:26:17.970 --> 01:26:20.264
But look out.

01:26:20.389 --> 01:26:22.474
It could be one so easily.

01:26:23.350 --> 01:26:27.438
- They don't like strangers, eh?
- No, they don't like anybody.

01:26:28.772 --> 01:26:32.234
Wild, you never saw
our friend here shoot, right?

01:26:34.361 --> 01:26:35.988
No.

01:26:36.906 --> 01:26:39.074
Did any of you?

01:26:41.660 --> 01:26:44.246
We don't know
how you'd be in emergencies.

01:26:45.873 --> 01:26:48.417
I was thinking,
this is the right place.

01:26:48.876 --> 01:26:51.795
I got a way you can show the men.

01:26:53.589 --> 01:26:54.798
How's that?

01:26:56.050 --> 01:26:57.968
Go into town alone, <i>amigo.</i>

01:29:44.760 --> 01:29:46.011
Bravo.

01:30:36.103 --> 01:30:39.064
Do you mind telling me
how you got here?

01:30:39.189 --> 01:30:41.942
I just reasoned it out.

01:30:42.067 --> 01:30:43.861
I figured you'd tell Indio

01:30:43.986 --> 01:30:47.364
to do just exactly the opposite
of what we agreed.

01:30:47.489 --> 01:30:50.576
And he's suspicious enough
to figure out something else.

01:30:51.577 --> 01:30:55.581
Since El Paso was out of the question,
well, here I am.

01:30:57.374 --> 01:30:59.376
Rum, a double.

01:31:00.252 --> 01:31:02.337
Tequila for all of us.

01:31:18.103 --> 01:31:22.149
Well, well, if it isn't the smoker.

01:31:23.734 --> 01:31:25.527
Well...

01:31:33.744 --> 01:31:36.455
Remember me, <i>amigo</i>?

01:31:36.580 --> 01:31:39.500
Of course you do.

01:31:39.625 --> 01:31:41.668
El Paso.

01:31:44.713 --> 01:31:46.507
It's a small world.

01:31:46.632 --> 01:31:49.927
Yes, and very, very bad.

01:31:50.052 --> 01:31:53.597
Now, come on.
You light another match.

01:31:55.140 --> 01:31:57.184
I generally smoke just after I eat.

01:31:57.309 --> 01:31:59.895
Why don't you come back
in about ten minutes?

01:32:00.020 --> 01:32:02.773
Ten minutes,
you'll be smoking in hell.

01:32:02.898 --> 01:32:06.068
- Get up!
- Stay calm.

01:32:07.402 --> 01:32:09.655
On your feet!

01:32:16.954 --> 01:32:18.830
Cuccillo...

01:32:19.915 --> 01:32:21.375
...count to three.

01:32:31.218 --> 01:32:33.136
One.

01:32:35.681 --> 01:32:36.723
Two.

01:32:39.142 --> 01:32:40.185
Three!

01:32:43.647 --> 01:32:45.607
Stop it!

01:33:07.504 --> 01:33:09.339
Who are you?

01:33:11.008 --> 01:33:12.884
I'm the one
who could open the safe for you.

01:33:17.431 --> 01:33:19.057
What safe, señor?

01:33:19.558 --> 01:33:22.519
The one from El Paso.
You got there ahead of me.

01:33:22.644 --> 01:33:24.521
- However...
- However?

01:33:26.440 --> 01:33:29.109
Open that safe and you're gonna destroy
half the bank notes.

01:33:30.277 --> 01:33:32.988
I can open it without blowing it up.

01:33:41.246 --> 01:33:42.706
What'll it cost?

01:33:43.665 --> 01:33:45.500
Five thousand.

01:33:47.502 --> 01:33:48.920
Two is all I'll pay you.

01:33:50.881 --> 01:33:52.633
Five.

01:34:29.461 --> 01:34:31.296
Keep your hands off it!

01:34:31.421 --> 01:34:35.050
It's easy to steal.
The trouble is in keeping the loot.

01:34:35.175 --> 01:34:37.010
Take it out.

01:34:37.135 --> 01:34:39.221
Now, every man in New Mexico
is after us.

01:34:39.346 --> 01:34:41.765
All they have to do
is catch one of us with some of this money,

01:34:41.890 --> 01:34:43.725
and we'll all end up the same way.

01:34:43.850 --> 01:34:46.019
We're going to wait here
for an entire month

01:34:46.144 --> 01:34:47.688
if I think it's necessary.

01:34:47.813 --> 01:34:50.732
Then everybody will get his share.

01:34:50.857 --> 01:34:53.110
And you'll wait a month
to get your money.

01:34:53.777 --> 01:34:56.154
Huh! Naturally.

01:34:56.279 --> 01:34:58.031
I'll be in the tavern.

01:34:58.156 --> 01:35:01.618
The air around here stinks anyway,
just like the food.

01:35:02.828 --> 01:35:04.913
But the month will go fast.

01:35:34.860 --> 01:35:36.319
All right.

01:35:44.786 --> 01:35:46.538
Right here.

01:35:47.289 --> 01:35:49.082
Let's go.

01:38:12.559 --> 01:38:14.561
Shh!

01:38:14.686 --> 01:38:17.063
I was worried about you.

01:38:17.188 --> 01:38:21.067
All alone with so many problems
to solve.

01:38:37.876 --> 01:38:38.960
It's all right here.

01:38:45.050 --> 01:38:46.509
Go ahead.

01:39:55.036 --> 01:39:57.789
You shouldn't have shot
the apples off that tree.

01:40:09.509 --> 01:40:11.344
Put it on.

01:42:00.703 --> 01:42:01.788
Stop it!

01:42:05.125 --> 01:42:08.086
Niño, see that they are tied securely.
Slim, keep your eye on them.

01:42:08.211 --> 01:42:10.004
Why let 'em live?

01:42:11.422 --> 01:42:13.675
All things at the right time.

01:42:13.800 --> 01:42:14.926
What do you mean?

01:42:15.051 --> 01:42:17.595
What's he doing now,
this sheriff of El Paso?

01:42:17.720 --> 01:42:21.099
Right now?
Looking for the cash that was in the bank.

01:42:22.100 --> 01:42:23.768
Right.

01:42:23.893 --> 01:42:28.815
And suppose he finds the bodies
of these men just outside El Paso

01:42:28.940 --> 01:42:31.151
with lots of money on them?

01:42:32.694 --> 01:42:34.571
What will the sheriff think?

01:42:34.696 --> 01:42:37.574
- Well, he...
- That's right.

01:43:56.736 --> 01:43:58.321
Slim.

01:44:01.532 --> 01:44:03.326
What is it, Niño?

01:44:04.953 --> 01:44:07.247
A change of plans.

01:44:07.372 --> 01:44:09.540
Indio wants you to...

01:44:50.540 --> 01:44:52.417
It's not loaded.

01:45:16.691 --> 01:45:19.277
I think you should get out fast now.

01:45:19.402 --> 01:45:21.821
Here's your guns without bullets.

01:45:22.739 --> 01:45:25.575
And listen, don't you let Indio
find you both around.

01:46:13.790 --> 01:46:17.502
I know you don't like questions, Indio,
but why are you doing this?

01:46:18.461 --> 01:46:20.171
Niño,

01:46:20.296 --> 01:46:23.674
how long have you known
that Manco's a bounty killer?

01:46:25.259 --> 01:46:27.512
I found out tonight. Why?

01:46:30.681 --> 01:46:34.143
I knew he was one
from the first moment he arrived.

01:46:39.524 --> 01:46:41.943
The other one's also a bounty killer.

01:46:43.986 --> 01:46:46.155
So, I have an idea.

01:46:46.280 --> 01:46:47.865
They'll be useful to us.

01:46:49.617 --> 01:46:51.494
We'll try it.

01:46:52.328 --> 01:46:55.248
Those men are a lot better
than mine with a gun.

01:46:56.332 --> 01:46:59.252
So, we'll let all of them
get mixed up in a gun battle.

01:47:00.336 --> 01:47:03.214
But that won't really matter to me.

01:47:05.758 --> 01:47:07.135
Or you.

01:47:09.429 --> 01:47:12.223
Because we'll be far away, right?

01:47:17.937 --> 01:47:20.523
And we'll have all the money.

01:47:23.192 --> 01:47:25.278
Go on.

01:47:25.403 --> 01:47:27.780
Go on and wake Cuccillo.

01:48:17.371 --> 01:48:18.539
Who did it?

01:48:19.207 --> 01:48:21.209
Why don't you look at the knife?

01:48:30.176 --> 01:48:31.385
It's mine.

01:48:32.011 --> 01:48:34.430
Then it shouldn't be there,
should it?

01:48:41.270 --> 01:48:44.023
Oh!

01:48:44.148 --> 01:48:47.235
But I didn't kill him, Indio.
I didn't do it.

01:48:48.069 --> 01:48:51.489
Cuccillo, it's difficult to prove that.

01:48:52.365 --> 01:48:55.826
Indio, I am innocent.

01:48:56.786 --> 01:48:59.247
One of your horses is outside.

01:48:59.997 --> 01:49:02.250
Let's see if you can get to it.

01:49:29.694 --> 01:49:31.112
Indio.

01:49:45.084 --> 01:49:46.627
Cuccillo...

01:49:50.047 --> 01:49:52.049
He just killed Slim.

01:49:54.093 --> 01:49:57.805
And he... he helped
those two bounty killers get away.

01:49:57.930 --> 01:49:59.807
I...

01:50:01.559 --> 01:50:03.311
I want them back.

01:50:04.770 --> 01:50:06.480
Right now.

01:50:08.733 --> 01:50:10.401
Right now.

01:50:12.528 --> 01:50:14.280
Right now!

01:50:19.452 --> 01:50:21.412
What are you doing here?

01:50:21.537 --> 01:50:24.206
Go and get them back!

01:50:25.875 --> 01:50:27.418
Groggy...

01:50:28.669 --> 01:50:30.713
Those two bounty killers
are sitting on our backs,

01:50:30.838 --> 01:50:33.633
and I tell you
they both must be killed right away.

01:50:38.387 --> 01:50:40.389
We can't let them go free.

01:50:55.196 --> 01:50:56.781
It's done now.

01:50:58.783 --> 01:51:00.993
Prepare to get out of here.

01:51:44.161 --> 01:51:45.871
- Here, Niño.
- Indio.

01:51:47.707 --> 01:51:49.500
Hold it.

01:51:53.963 --> 01:51:56.382
Not a bad idea, Indio.

01:51:56.507 --> 01:51:58.801
But I'm one thing you forgot about.

01:51:58.926 --> 01:52:00.594
Open it up now.

01:52:22.408 --> 01:52:24.452
All right, come on now, open it.

01:53:23.636 --> 01:53:25.888
Leave Indio to me.

01:53:28.641 --> 01:53:30.309
All right.

01:54:02.633 --> 01:54:04.802
Where in hell is it?

01:54:32.705 --> 01:54:36.083
I'll kill them,
but I'll rip out their guts first.

01:54:36.208 --> 01:54:38.502
I have a plan, Groggy.

01:54:45.050 --> 01:54:46.677
What?

01:54:47.344 --> 01:54:49.221
Let's just wait, Groggy.

01:54:49.346 --> 01:54:51.432
They'll be back here.

01:54:54.226 --> 01:54:56.729
And this way, there'll be two of us.

01:54:56.854 --> 01:54:59.815
Can they come back here?
Your men could've killed them.

01:54:59.940 --> 01:55:01.859
Who? They?

01:55:06.280 --> 01:55:08.991
Are you sure of that, Indio?
That they haven't?

01:55:12.369 --> 01:55:14.496
I thought something different.

01:55:14.622 --> 01:55:19.710
You made the boys ride on out
to make sure they're both killed and fast.

01:55:20.419 --> 01:55:23.172
I'm not as dumb
as the rest of them, Indio.

01:55:24.089 --> 01:55:26.050
There was no help for it.

01:56:59.643 --> 01:57:01.270
Go on.

01:58:10.214 --> 01:58:12.007
Back there.

01:58:48.919 --> 01:58:50.504
That watch...

01:58:51.839 --> 01:58:54.633
It's been a long time that I wanted to ask.

01:58:56.135 --> 01:58:58.846
I can see that it means a lot to you, Indio.

01:58:58.971 --> 01:59:00.722
Why?

02:00:33.023 --> 02:00:35.692
Indio!

02:00:37.069 --> 02:00:38.987
Listen to me!

02:00:40.614 --> 02:00:42.824
This is Colonel Mortimer!

02:00:45.244 --> 02:00:47.329
Douglas Mortimer!

02:00:49.164 --> 02:00:52.042
Does the name mean anything to you?

02:02:24.426 --> 02:02:27.763
When the chimes end,
pick up your gun.

02:02:28.555 --> 02:02:30.682
Try and shoot me, Colonel.

02:02:32.726 --> 02:02:34.895
Just try.

02:04:29.885 --> 02:04:32.429
Very careless of you, old man.

02:04:58.246 --> 02:04:59.998
Try this.

02:05:07.339 --> 02:05:09.216
Now we start.

02:07:00.118 --> 02:07:01.244
Bravo.

02:07:42.577 --> 02:07:45.413
There seems to be
a family resemblance.

02:07:51.628 --> 02:07:53.421
Here.

02:07:57.759 --> 02:08:01.054
Naturally, between brother and sister.

02:08:01.179 --> 02:08:02.931
My gun.

02:08:07.644 --> 02:08:11.272
My boy, you've become rich.

02:08:12.399 --> 02:08:15.110
You mean we've become rich, old man.

02:08:15.235 --> 02:08:18.279
No, it's all for you.
I think you deserve it.

02:08:19.197 --> 02:08:20.740
What about our partnership?

02:08:24.077 --> 02:08:26.413
Maybe next time.

02:09:08.329 --> 02:09:10.290
Ten thousand.

02:09:10.415 --> 02:09:12.333
Twelve thousand.

02:09:12.459 --> 02:09:14.294
Fifteen.

02:09:15.628 --> 02:09:17.005
Sixteen.

02:09:17.714 --> 02:09:19.549
Seventeen.

02:09:19.674 --> 02:09:21.509
Twenty-two.

02:09:22.469 --> 02:09:24.387
Twenty-two.

02:09:26.681 --> 02:09:28.266
Argh!

02:09:29.642 --> 02:09:31.728
Twenty-seven.

02:09:33.521 --> 02:09:34.856
Any trouble, boy?

02:09:37.275 --> 02:09:39.486
No, old man.

02:09:40.361 --> 02:09:42.947
Thought I was having trouble
with my adding.

02:09:44.115 --> 02:09:46.451
It's all right now.
